V1 - Somewhere in 1992, could start only 10 programs.
V2 - Somewhere in 1992, could already start 30 programs.
V3.00 - 29 & 30/09/93
V3.01 - 25/11/93
V3.02 - 07 & 08/12/93
V3.03 - 22/01/94
V3.04 & V3.05 - 02/03/94 -> V3.05 is a different version without opal font 12.
V3.06 - 13/03/94
V3.07 & V3.08 - 20/03/94
V3.09 - 21 & 22/03/94
V3.10 - 23/03/94
V3.11 - 28/03/94
V3.12 - 10/04/94 Removed search bug.
V3.13 - 24/04/94 Removed memorychecking.
V3.14 - 01/05/94 Added new routine, search for (a) string(s) and show(ing) it/them with an arrow. + removed some bugs.
V3.15 - 09/05/94 Added a check for the font in ROM. If no, check FONTS: + Removed bug in verttext[].
V3.16 - 24/05/94 Added new routine 'Auto Screen Swap'. Due to a bug in AmosPro, interlace screens might be corrupt the first time the program is started.
V3.17 - 27/07/94 Swapped Wait Vbl with Vbl Wait 0 and Draw with F Draw. SPEEEEEED !!!!!!!!!
V3.18 - 11/08/94 Cleaned up the code and partially rewritten.
V3.19 - 14 & 15/08/94 New save-format !! 'DMX94.8' !! This one is about «180» bytes shorter !!!
V3.19b - 22 & 23/08/94 Adjusted the new save-format a little. Saving in DMX93.10 & DMX94.8 format is possible now. But the ASCII-converter can't work with the new format.
V3.20 - 23/08/94 Added a new Procedure (VOEGIN). Made a slight adjustment to the load-routine (is a tiny bit faster now).
V3.21 - 26/08/94 Small bug removed. Output files are 60-80 bytes smaller.
V3.22 - 29 & 30/08/94 Adjusted save-format a little. + Removed some bugs, so a couple of routines now work, again ;)
V3.23 - 04/09/94 Bug-fix. If no (or wrong) file was loaded, one menuitem was empty.
V3.24 - 09/09/94 Replaced load-routines V1,2 & 3 by One (1) routine. + MAAT$() now uses the READ - instruction.
V3.25 - 11/09/94 Added a built-in SCREENBLANKER. When you put the 'Menu' screen at the foreground for 3 mins, the screens becomes black (simplicity rulezzzz :)
V3.26 - 30/09/94 Killed a few load & input-routine bugs. + New menuitem added.
V3.27 - 26/11/94 *NEW* ą A routine to start a program by pressing the button-no (press i). ˛ During loading nothing can be started anymore.
V3.30 Alpha - 11 & 17 & 18/12/94 Testing a Resource Routine.
V3.30 Beta - 01/01/95 Resource Routine finished with routines from the proc MENOPT[]. And did a partial rewrite.
V3.31 - 15 & 16/01/95 Kicked a menuitem. Removed the routines MenuIn,MenuUit,FutureMenus en MenuControl. Else the program couldn't be compiled anymore.
        Rewrote the code a little bit. Auto Screen Swap ALWAYS ON now.
  ''  - 21/01/95 Kicked a bug from VOEGIN[]. Wouldn't save a new file anymore.
V3.40 - 16 & 17/04/95 Rewrote the entire load-routine. The file will be loaded in a membank in one go now. Loading is about 5.9x faster now :))
  ''  - 19/04/95 Removed small text error.
***** From V3.41+ this program is now semi-intelligent. This is due to some search-routines, that search the data actively, are now smaller and faster (I know it sounds crap, but it works :).
V3.41 - 26/04/95 Rewrote the search-routines. Now there much more compact (1 proc).
  ''  - 27/04/95 Rewrote proc. Vak1 & Vak2. Rewrote proc. Teksten.
V3.42 - 28/04/95 Rewrote the mouse-handler routine.
  ''  - 26/05/95 Removed small save-bug.
  ''  - 24/06/95 Changed the exec-routine slightly.
V3.43 - 21 & 22/07/95 Made an improved load & save-routine (95.7). Cleaned the input-routine.
  ''  - 02/08/95 Removed a small save-bug. + If pressing 'S', the wrong (old) format was used.
  ''  - 18/10/95 Removed small bug.
  ''  - 11/02/98 New AMOS.LIBRARY(2.21). YEAH!!! Removed a small bug.
  ''  - 19/07/98 Added a version string ($VER).
V3.44 - 19/07/98 When executing Lexecute will be used now. + Ldisk Font commando added.
V3.43B & 3.44Beta2 - 04/08/98 Removed some silly errors in the helptext.
V3.43C & 3.44Beta3 - 13/08/98 Small changes.
V3.44Beta4 - 13/08/98 Swapped the old font routine with a couple of routines from 'Easylife'. + Removed some stupid bugs.
V3.44Beta5 - 26/09/98 Cleanup. Removed old rem's. Changed the routine INLADEN[]. Saved 1766 bytes.
V3.44Beta6 - 15 & 16/12/98 New amos.library(2.30) !?! This one gives another outcome of ->AMOS HERE<- ; Was -1, is now 255.
WARNING: !!! AMOS HERE is in the editor -1 and compiled 255 (sometimes) !!!!!
